  "text": "The Kafka-to-Flink serialization boundary spans two repos. On the Kafka side (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489), the core interfaces are defined in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/serialization/: Serializer<T> (objects to bytes), Deserializer<T> (bytes to objects), Serde<T> (wraps both), and Serdes (factory class with WrapperSerde). On the Flink side (sg-evals/flink--0cc95fcc), the parallel interfaces live in flink-core/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/api/common/serialization/: DeserializationSchema<T> and SerializationSchema<T> define the Flink-native contract for byte-level serialization, with AbstractDeserializationSchema<T> providing type-inference support. The bridge classes that implement Flink's DeserializationSchema and SerializationSchema for Kafka use cases are SimpleStringSchema (explicitly labeled 'Kafka Serialization'), ByteArraySchema (also labeled 'Kafka Serialization'), and TypeInformationSerializationSchema. A concrete Kafka-specific example is EventDeSerializationSchema in flink-examples, which implements both Flink interfaces and is used with KafkaRecordDeserializationSchema.valueOnly() to bridge Kafka records into Flink's processing pipeline. Note: in this Flink version, the Kafka connector (flink-connector-kafka) has been externalized to a separate repository, so the KafkaDeserializationSchema and KafkaRecordDeserializationSchema interfaces are not in the flink--0cc95fcc mirror itself; the boundary within this mirror is formed by Flink's core serialization interfaces and the bridge schemas that implement them for Kafka data.",
